  "response_text": "At dusk in a stylized city, a large illuminated rooftop billboard stands among high-rise buildings under a purple-blue sky. The billboard has a teal background. On the left is a large white jug of Clorox Ultra Bleach with a green cap and the familiar oval Clorox label. To the right, big white lettering reads, “NEW ULTRA CLOROX BLEACH GETS WHITES EVEN WHITER,” though the final word is partly being covered with pale green paint.\n\nTwo animated bleach-bottle characters are on the narrow platform in front of the billboard. Both are white plastic jug-like figures with faces, arms, and “BARGAIN BLEACH” printed across their bodies. One is tall and slim, wearing a red-and-yellow cap turned sideways; the other is shorter and rounder, with thick dark eyebrows and a small blue cap. The squat character holds a paint roller and is actively painting over the word “WHITER” on the sign. A paint tray and small paint container sit on the platform between them. The taller character stands beside him, watching and gesturing as the green paint spreads over the letters.\n\nCloser to the billboard, the large Clorox product image fills the left side while the two bargain-bleach characters occupy the platform below the text. The squat character continues rolling paint across the bright white letters, while the taller one looks on with wide eyes. The roller moves between the paint tray and the billboard. As they interact, the taller character gestures with one hand as if arguing or cautioning, while the squat character keeps a confident, determined expression and points or waves the roller toward the sign. The green paint sits in uneven patches over the word, but the original white letters are still partly visible underneath.\n\nThe squat character becomes more animated with the roller, swinging it upward and splattering light-colored paint. The taller character recoils, raises his hands, and briefly covers his face as drops of paint scatter near him and across the billboard. The squat character looks pleased with himself, while the taller one appears startled and annoyed, his body pulled back and his eyes widened.\n\nThe scene changes to a product demonstration on a plain teal-blue background. A single long white sock appears tilted diagonally, but it is visibly gray and brown with heavy dirt stains. The word “BEFORE” appears in small white capital letters near the upper left of the sock. The dirty sock remains on the left as the screen becomes divided vertically. On the right, a matching sock appears bright, clean, and white, with the text “NEW ULTRA CLOROX BLEACH” above it. The contrast is clear: the left sock is dingy and stained, while the right sock is much whiter. A small “Dramatization” note appears near the bottom as the comparison overlaps briefly with the billboard imagery.\n\nBack on the rooftop, the billboard again dominates the scene, with the large Clorox jug on the left and the bold claim across the teal background. The word “WHITER” is still smeared with pale green paint, and the two bargain-bleach characters stand below it on the rooftop surface. The taller one, in the red-and-yellow cap, stands near a paint can and looks concerned; the squat one stands beside him, still looking self-satisfied.\n\nThe setting then shifts to a closer, gray industrial-looking backdrop with tall arched windows behind the characters. The two animated bargain-bleach bottles stand on a rough surface littered with small paint splatters and tools. A small can labeled “BARGAIN PAINT” sits to the left. The tall bottle holds a green sponge or paint-covered pad in one hand and the paint can in the other, raising the sponge as he talks or demonstrates. The squat bottle holds the paint roller and watches him with narrowed, skeptical eyes. The tall character lifts the green pad higher, looking upward with an anxious open-mouthed expression, while the squat character shifts the roller and glares. The tall bottle continues gesturing with the can and pad; the squat one reacts with a smug or annoyed look, keeping the roller close to his body.\n\nThe final images return to the billboard, now cleanly presented as a product sign without the animated characters in front. The large white Clorox Ultra Bleach jug with green cap is on the left. On the right, bold white text reads, “NEW ULTRA CLOROX BLEACH GETS WHITES EVEN WHITER.” The teal billboard is lit by metal lamps along the top, with the purple evening skyline and surrounding buildings visible behind it.",
